		<link rel="stylesheet" href="css/stylesheet.css" />
	</head>
	
	<body>
		<h1>Reference Manual</h1>
		
		<a href="index.html"><h3>Return to index</h3></a>
		
		<h2>Key Features:</h2>
		<ul class="large-list">
			<li>
				<h3>Legend:</h3>
				<p>The user-interface, when attempting to complete a board, includes a legend of all of its components.</p>
			</li>
			<li>
				<h3>Loads Progress:</h3>
				<p>If the user has completed a board, their progress will have been saved. If the user terminates the program, and then returns to it, their progress will
				be loaded automatically.</p>
			</li>
			<li>
				<h3>Navigation Menus for Improved Ease-of-use:</h3>
				<p>Throughout the program, there are navigation menus implemented, to improve the organization of sections and make it easier to use the program. There is a 
				navigation menu to look through boards as well as components</p>
			</li>
			<li>
				<h3>Restarting/resetting:</h3>
				<p>If the user returns to the board-list during a game, and clicks on the same board again, their game will have been reset.</p>
			</li>		
			<li>
				<h3>Saving:</h3>
				<p>This program saves your score every time you complete a board; if you re-do a board and get a worse score, the new score will be recorded, regardless.</p>
			</li>
		</ul>
	</body>
</html>